02:39.077 --> 02:41.246
(HEAVY BREATHING CONTINUES)

02:41.830 --> 02:43.790
QUINLAN: How compromised is the scene?

02:43.915 --> 02:45.334
GIBSON: They did a pretty good job of it.

02:45.625 --> 02:47.836
(INDISTINCT CHATTER ON POLICE RADIO)

02:49.254 --> 02:50.922
GIBSON: Already dead when we arrived.

02:59.848 --> 03:02.142
(HEAVY BREATHING CONTINUES)

03:04.519 --> 03:05.604
Oh, my God.

03:08.190 --> 03:10.525
It wasn't just the mothers.
It was the dads, too.

03:10.984 --> 03:12.069
The thing about fundraisers...

03:12.152 --> 03:13.820
Everybody wants to prove who's the richest.

03:13.945 --> 03:14.946
They're vicious.

03:15.030 --> 03:17.616
Add alcohol to the mix
and the fact that women don't let things go...

03:17.699 --> 03:20.452
They're like the Olympic athletes of grudges.

03:20.535 --> 03:22.662
It's sexist how the women always get blamed.

03:22.788 --> 03:24.956
It all goes back to that incident
on orientation day.

03:25.999 --> 03:28.877
And at the root of it was Madeline Mackenzie.

03:30.212 --> 03:33.673
There's nothing to be nervous about.
Your sister loved going there, and so will you.

03:33.799 --> 03:36.635
In fact, you should be excited.
Do you know why?

03:37.302 --> 03:42.307
Because this is the very first day
of the rest of your life.

03:43.141 --> 03:44.351
Okay, woman.

03:44.476 --> 03:46.853
I am not 100% sure
about that tone, young lady.

03:46.978 --> 03:49.147
And could you please turn it down, please?

03:51.400 --> 03:52.734
Thank you.

03:54.403 --> 03:55.487
(BRAKES SQUEALING)

03:55.570 --> 03:56.905
- Mother...
- CHLOE: Fucker.

03:57.906 --> 03:59.324
(SIGHS) Chloe Adeline Mackenzie.

03:59.574 --> 04:01.827
- You were thinking it.
- Because I was scared.

04:02.202 --> 04:04.663
Do you want to see how teenagers die?
This is how.

04:04.746 --> 04:07.374
This young lady in front of me
is driving and texting at the same time.

04:07.499 --> 04:08.500
(HORN HONKING)

04:08.667 --> 04:10.043
MADELINE: You're going to...

04:10.836 --> 04:12.212
This is just...

04:12.504 --> 04:13.839
I'll be right back.

04:15.590 --> 04:16.757
They're dead.

04:19.719 --> 04:22.180
GIRL 1: Don't reply yet.
GIRL 2: Yes, I have to reply.

04:22.264 --> 04:24.307
- That's not...
- Excuse me. You must stop.

04:24.391 --> 04:25.767
- You're going to kill yourself or...
- Mom?

04:25.851 --> 04:28.186
- What is your problem?
- Abigail, what are you doing?

04:28.270 --> 04:29.938
You were supposed to be on the bus.

04:30.689 --> 04:31.690
She picked me up, okay?

04:31.773 --> 04:33.233
You know how I feel
about you driving with texters.

04:33.358 --> 04:35.360
- Mom.
- It is worse than drinking and driving.

04:35.444 --> 04:36.695
Get out of the car.

04:37.028 --> 04:38.697
I'm not getting out of the car.

04:38.780 --> 04:41.158
- We're three blocks from school, okay?
- Fine.

04:41.241 --> 04:44.077
- ABIGAIL: You're being ridiculous.
- If I catch you driving and texting again,

04:44.202 --> 04:45.203
- I will find your mother...
- ABIGAIL: Mom!

04:45.287 --> 04:46.746
-...and I will throw this at her.
- ABIGAIL: Don't...

04:49.458 --> 04:50.542
(GROANS)

04:50.792 --> 04:54.629
it's possible that had she not fallen,
nobody would've gotten killed.

04:55.714 --> 04:56.756
JANE: Ouch.

04:56.965 --> 05:00.469
