Look at our life.

31:31.433 --> 31:33.894
What kind of person chooses to work?

31:33.977 --> 31:37.856
Certainly not a mother,
by any acceptable standards.

31:39.149 --> 31:40.233
(SIGHS)

31:40.317 --> 31:42.277
You should have seen
the way they looked at me today.

31:42.360 --> 31:43.695
(CHUCKLES) on, my God.

31:46.448 --> 31:50.327
And on the one morning
that I chose not to go to the office...

31:50.410 --> 31:53.205
- Yep.
-...and join my daughter for her orientation,

31:54.039 --> 31:56.917
and then defend her
when she's physically assaulted.

31:58.752 --> 32:04.758
And, yes, I reacted humanly
like any mom would.

32:07.886 --> 32:10.347
And then I'm met with utter contempt.

32:10.430 --> 32:14.184
Look, I'm sure there are those,
women especially, who would resent you.

32:14.267 --> 32:16.311
I mean, look at you. Come on.

32:16.394 --> 32:19.815
You're beautiful, hugely successful,
financially independent,

32:19.898 --> 32:23.110
on the school committee,
the board of the aquarium.

32:23.193 --> 32:24.236
Huh?

32:25.153 --> 32:26.947
- Right?
- Yeah.

32:30.450 --> 32:31.785
Hell yeah.

32:33.453 --> 32:35.997
And to make matters even worse,

32:37.874 --> 32:41.628
you're beyond sexy.

32:44.047 --> 32:46.007
- Mmm.
-(CHUCKLES)

32:51.680 --> 32:52.973
Women.

32:53.056 --> 32:58.270
You all want to be the envy of your friends,
but God forbid you garner too much of it.

33:12.492 --> 33:15.662
The mom was awful, but the girl seemed fine.

33:16.246 --> 33:17.581
<i>JAN E'S</i> MOM: <i>So what's going to happen?</i>

33:18.081 --> 33:19.124
Um...

33:19.666 --> 33:24.838
I don't know. The teacher said
that we should just let it go, move forward.

33:24.921 --> 33:26.882
So I guess that's what we're going to do.

33:28.341 --> 33:31.303
<i>I still don't understand
why you chose to move there</i>

33:31.386 --> 33:33.054
<i>all alone.</i>

33:33.138 --> 33:35.015
I'm not. I have friends.

33:35.098 --> 33:37.100
People here are actually very friendly.

33:37.184 --> 33:38.852
<i>People need family in their lives, you know?</i>

33:38.935 --> 33:40.562
<i>I really just think
you should come back here...</i>

33:40.645 --> 33:42.856
Do we have to get into this
every single time we talk?

33:45.358 --> 33:46.860
I'm gonna go check on Ziggy.

33:49.070 --> 33:50.572
Jesus.

33:59.915 --> 34:01.374
(MOBILE RINGING)

34:02.000 --> 34:03.043
JAN E'S MOM: <i>Hello.</i>

34:03.376 --> 34:05.962
Hey, Mom. I'm sorry.

34:08.089 --> 34:09.466
I love you.

34:10.425 --> 34:11.676
<i>I love...</i>

34:21.561 --> 34:22.812
(WATER DRIPPING)

35:28.837 --> 35:30.088
(WHISPERING) Hi, baby.

35:31.423 --> 35:32.924
Sorry I woke you up.

35:34.551 --> 35:36.177
Am I in trouble?

35:36.803 --> 35:38.471
No, of course not.

35:43.018 --> 35:44.978
You trust me, right?

35:45.520 --> 35:47.105
And I trust you.

35:49.190 --> 35:51.192
Did you touch that little girl, baby?

35:52.027 --> 35:53.611
It's okay if you did.

36:00.035 --> 36:01.202
Ziggy?

36:02.287 --> 36:03.330
No.

36:04.372 --> 36:05.498
Okay.

36:07.083 --> 36:08.376
I believe you.

36:09.586 --> 36:11.296
Why did she say I did?

36:12.380 --> 36:13.673
I don't know.

36:13.757 --> 36:16.593
Maybe she was confused.
She probably just got it wrong.

36:17.886 --> 36:19.554
Am I going to have any friends?

36:19.637 --> 36:21.514
Of course you are, my love.

36:21.598 --> 36:23.767
You're going to have so many friends.

36:26.519 --> 36:27.854
Come here.

36:29.814 --> 36:30.940
(KISSES)

36:32.692 --> 36:34.402
-(SIGHS)
-(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

36:34.819 --> 36:35.904
Yeah?

36:38.573 --> 36:43.411
Honey, I think we need to talk about
the SAT tutor.

36:43.495 --> 36:44.621
Oh, Mom.

36:44.704 --> 36:45.830
I know what you're going to say,

36:45.914 --> 36:48.249
but your scores just aren't good enough
right now, honey, and I...

36:48.333 --> 36:51.002
You know, the whole college thing,
it's kind of a racket.

36:51.086 --> 36:52.879
Especially liberal arts.

36:52.962 --> 36:54.798
People go off and study Homer for four years,

36:54.881 --> 36:57.675
and then you graduate with a ton of debt
and no job prospects.

36:57.759 --> 36:59.636
Okay, let me be clear.

37:00.512 --> 37:03.264
You're going to college.

37:03.348 --> 37:06.768
- Ed didn't go, and he's doing all right.
- Yeah, but Ed studied computer engineering.

37:06.851 --> 37:08.186
Do you want to be a computer engineer?

37:08.269 --> 37:11.272
And Dad, he never went,
and he seems perfectly happy in life.

37:11.481 --> 37:12.649
(SIGHS)

37:12.732 --> 37:14.150
Career-wise.

37:14.651 --> 37:17.612
Okay, well, let's just finish that analogy.
Let's not leave Bonnie out of this.

37:17.695 --> 37:21.366
Her little cup just runneth over
with happiness, doesn't it?

37:21.449 --> 37:23.410
With no college degree at all.

37:24.202 --> 37:27.163
I'm sorry that you hate Bonnie
and that I'm unable to.

37:27.247 --> 37:28.373
I don't hate Bonnie.

37:28.456 --> 37:30.708
And this isn't about your dad
or Bonnie or me.

37:30.792 --> 37:32.919
This is about you, Abigail, and your future.

37:33.002 --> 37:34.212
And what I'm saying is,

37:34.295 --> 37:36.965
the metric of success is not always
monetary or career-related.

37:37.048 --> 37:38.883
It can be a much more holistic equation.

37:38.967 --> 37:41.428
Okay, I'm not gonna pretend
to be the person in your life

37:41.511 --> 37:44.514
who knows the most about
the holistic wonder of the world.

37:45.014 --> 37:48.935
What I do know,
and I know this for sure, Abigail,

37:49.436 --> 37:51.729
is that, when it all comes down to it,

37:51.813 --> 37:54.816
you have to be independent,
and you have to be self-sufficient.

37:54.899 --> 37:57.235
I was a very young mother when I had you.

37:57.318 --> 38:00.947
All that it-takes-a-village crap
is only good to a certain extent

38:01.030 --> 38:04.576
because even the best-laid plans of your life
go poof in your face,

38:04.659 --> 38:07.245
and, in that case, you need to be strong

38:07.328 --> 38:11.249
and independent and educated
and a strong woman.

38:11.332 --> 38:13.084
You said "strong" twice.

38:15.128 --> 38:17.881
You kind of remind me of a space alien
right now. You know that?

38:20.341 --> 38:21.551
Good night.

38:21.718 --> 38:22.760
(SIGHS DEEPLY)

38:26.556 --> 38:27.682
No.

38:38.526 --> 38:40.278
PERRY:
"E is for Ernest, who choked on a peach.

38:41.905 --> 38:42.906
(BOYS CHUCKLE)

38:42.989 --> 38:46.326
"F is for Fanny, sucked dry by a leech."

38:46.618 --> 38:48.661
-(PERRY MAKES SUCTION SOUNDS)
- BOYS: Ew!

38:48.870 --> 38:51.789
That's what you get if you go down
to the beach without me or your mom.

38:51.873 --> 38:53.374
- MAX: But...
- Strictly forbidden.

38:53.458 --> 38:54.709
There's too many leeches down there.

38:54.792 --> 38:57.420
MAX: The last time we went,
there was no leeches.

38:57.712 --> 39:00.882
PERRY: No, of course not 'cause I was there,
and they're scared of me.

39:01.549 --> 39:03.092
What, you didn't notice?

39:03.176 --> 39:05.720
Every time we go down there,
I just, like, scare them away.

39:06.262 --> 39:07.430
JOSH: How?

39:07.514 --> 39:10.683
PERRY: With my...
(BURPS) Burping superpower.

39:11.309 --> 39:12.393
(BOYS (assume)

39:14.312 --> 39:16.272
PERRY: Do you want to know a secret?
JOSH: What?

39:17.065 --> 39:21.236
My superpower, I actually get it from Mom.

39:21.778 --> 39:23.988
- BOY: No.
- PERRY: You don't believe me?

39:24.489 --> 39:26.908
What did we have for dinner tonight
with the steak?

39:29.285 --> 39:32.413
- BOY: Mom's spinach salad?
- PERRY: Mom's spinach salad.

39:32.997 --> 39:34.040
(PERRY IMITATING BURPING)

39:34.624 --> 39:35.667
(BOYS LAUGHING)

39:36.501 --> 39:38.127
PERRY: Top secret, okay?

39:38.878 --> 39:40.296
(CONTINUES IMITATING BURPING)

39:41.673 --> 39:45.218
"G is for George, smothered under a rug.

39:45.969 --> 39:49.305
"H is for Hector, done in by a thug."

39:52.934 --> 39:55.144
-(GASPS)
-(PERRY CHUCKLES)

39:55.395 --> 39:58.106
- You startled me.
- I'm sorry.

40:01.276 --> 40:03.069
- These are great.
- Mmm-hmm...

40:03.361 --> 40:04.404
Hmm.

40:07.657 --> 40:10.827
The boys mentioned something
about a little girl getting hurt today.

40:11.202 --> 40:12.245
Mmm.

40:13.037 --> 40:14.956
Renata Klein's daughter.

40:15.039 --> 40:17.792
She wasn't really injured. She was just...

40:18.835 --> 40:22.255
Oh, look at this. Could they be cuter?

40:23.006 --> 40:24.799
PERRY: Oh.
I actually think this is my favorite.

40:24.882 --> 40:27.010
- I love your finger there.
- Stop.

40:27.093 --> 40:28.344
- Post it.
- All right.

40:28.428 --> 40:29.887
People are gonna love it.

40:30.096 --> 40:31.139
(CELESTE LAUGHS)

40:31.556 --> 40:33.224
Well, so what happened?

40:33.308 --> 40:34.601
With that girl.

40:34.684 --> 40:36.311
A boy tried to choke her.

40:38.229 --> 40:39.439
Are you serious?

40:39.647 --> 40:40.732
(SIGHS)

40:40.815 --> 40:42.942
Well, no one witnessed it,

40:43.026 --> 40:45.612
but she was pretty distraught,
and she had marks on her neck.

40:46.112 --> 40:47.447
Which boy?

40:48.906 --> 40:52.035
Um, this new boy, Ziggy.

40:52.577 --> 40:55.288
I mean, he seemed really sweet,

40:55.371 --> 40:59.792
and I met his mom,
and she couldn't be nicer, so...

40:59.876 --> 41:01.044
Yeah.

41:02.211 --> 41:05.298
Well, to be safe, we should tell Josh and Max
to keep their distance from him.

41:06.424 --> 41:08.926
- I don't think that's gonna be necessary.
- Honey.

41:09.010 --> 41:11.638
- If the kid is violent, we don't...
- No, he's not violent.

41:11.721 --> 41:13.389
Well, how do you know he's not violent?

41:13.973 --> 41:15.683
What, because he seemed sweet?

41:18.394 --> 41:21.981
- First off, he could be innocent.
- Or he could be guilty.

41:23.232 --> 41:25.610
We don't want the boys to be
getting mixed up with the wrong crowd.

41:26.027 --> 41:28.279
- They're six.
- They're not to associate with him.

41:33.826 --> 41:35.787
You're being ridiculous.

41:37.038 --> 41:38.164
(CELESTE SIGHS)

41:38.331 --> 41:39.415
(CELESTE YELPS)

41:39.499 --> 41:42.669
- The boys will stay away from that kid.
- Take your hand off me.

41:42.752 --> 41:45.922
If I can't be here to look out for them,
I need to know that you do.

41:46.923 --> 41:49.926
I asked you to remove your fucking hand.

41:55.264 --> 41:56.599
(BREATH ES SHAKILY)

41:58.226 --> 41:59.811
(PLAYING PIANO)

42:03.106 --> 42:04.941
ABIGAIL:
Is that a song from your puppet show?

42:06.651 --> 42:09.654
Yes, but it's really more
than just a puppet show.

42:10.488 --> 42:11.531
(RESUMES PLAYING)

42:11.614 --> 42:13.533
<i>(SANGS SOFTLY) Four years of college</i>

42:13.616 --> 42:16.494
<i>And plenty of knowledge</i>

42:16.577 --> 42:20.748
<i>Have earned me this useless degree</i>

42:22.333 --> 42:24.001
The play means a lot to you, right?

42:27.463 --> 42:30.425
I'll tell Bonnie to start a new petition

42:31.008 --> 42:32.301
in favor.

42:35.179 --> 42:36.848
Mom, are you okay?

42:37.432 --> 42:39.475
You're not like dying or anything, are you?

42:40.643 --> 42:42.603
No, I'm not dying.

42:43.354 --> 42:44.731
What would make you ask me that?

42:45.148 --> 42:47.150
You seem a little wobbly.

42:47.692 --> 42:49.569
Are you having one of your massive periods?

42:49.652 --> 42:50.987
No.

42:52.196 --> 42:53.573
No.

42:55.742 --> 43:00.288
What people don't tell you
is that you lose your children.

43:02.915 --> 43:05.835
As beautiful and wonderful as you are now,

43:07.170 --> 43:10.423
the little girl whose curly hair
I used to detangle,

43:10.506 --> 43:14.093
the one who had bad dreams
and would crawl into my bed,

43:14.177 --> 43:15.386
she's gone.

43:18.389 --> 43:19.432
Yeah.

43:19.599 --> 43:21.267
And I guess that's why I'm feeling a little bit...

43:21.851 --> 43:25.772
Compounded by the fact
that your little sister's going to first grade.

43:27.899 --> 43:29.692
I'm losing my babies,

43:30.193 --> 43:34.197
which has been clinically compared
to a massive period, I think.

43:38.367 --> 43:40.369
I'll always be your baby.

43:41.871 --> 43:44.290
Bonnie's like a friend, you know?

43:44.540 --> 43:46.584
Maybe even a best friend sometimes.

43:47.460 --> 43:50.379
But I'm your daughter, and you're my mother.

43:53.800 --> 43:56.219
Mom, don't cry.

43:57.762 --> 44:00.431
- Don't do that, okay?
- I'm sorry.

44:00.765 --> 44:01.808
(ABIGAIL CHUCKLES)

44:02.058 --> 44:03.392
I'm sorry. (SNIFFLES)

44:07.438 --> 44:10.525
Your hair, though,
get it out of your beautiful face.

44:12.610 --> 44:14.737
I can still call you babycakes, can't I?

44:16.072 --> 44:18.032
- Not in public.
- Okay.

44:18.324 --> 44:19.367
-(BOTH CHUCKLING)
-(DOOR OPENS)

44:19.784 --> 44:20.952
Oh, no.

44:21.452 --> 44:23.746
Not another one. You go back to bed.

44:28.292 --> 44:30.086
(PLAYING PIANO)

44:39.178 --> 44:40.930
(HUMS ALONG SOFTLY)

44:43.766 --> 44:45.393
I love that song.

44:46.102 --> 44:47.436
Do you want to play it together?

44:48.646 --> 44:49.647
(INAUDIBLE)

44:58.781 --> 45:00.950
<i>We're treating the matter as a homicide.</i>

45:01.576 --> 45:03.953
<i>We have no suspects as of yet.</i>

45:30.813 --> 45:36.652
<i>I will say that we do believe we have spoken
to the person or persons involved.</i>

45:42.617 --> 45:43.784
Ziggy-

45:44.285 --> 45:45.411
Baby.

45:50.041 --> 45:51.459
What are we doing?

45:51.542 --> 45:53.210
You were sleepwalking again, baby.

46:05.389 --> 46:06.641
<i>CELESTE". Where are we
going to do the interview?</i>

46:06.724 --> 46:10.061
<i>QUIN</i> LAN: <i>Right here.
CELESTE: I'll just put my purse down here.</i>

46:12.563 --> 46:15.316
<i>NIPPAL: The first thing I said,
it wasn't just the mothers.</i>

46:15.691 --> 46:17.568
GABRIELLE: <i>It was the dads, too.</i>

46:17.652 --> 46:18.986
<i>STU: The thing about fundraisers...</i>

46:19.070 --> 46:20.321
<i>MELISSA: They're vicious.</i>

46:20.404 --> 46:22.907
<i>STU: It's not the male grizzlies
you've got to watch out for.</i>

46:23.491 --> 46:24.951
<i>It's the sow.</i>

46:26.243 --> 46:28.454
<i>GIBSON: Tell me about Celeste Wright.</i>

46:29.121 --> 46:30.414
<i>GABRIELLE: (SCOFFS)
Something had to be wrong.</i>

46:30.498 --> 46:32.750
JACKIE: So elegant, <i>so...</i>
MADELINE: Volcanic.

46:32.917 --> 46:34.168
Madeline Mackenzie?

46:34.293 --> 46:35.378
Things never blow over...

46:35.461 --> 46:36.963
<i>Once Madeline gets involved.</i>

46:37.129 --> 46:38.589
<i>They blow up.</i>

46:39.173 --> 46:42.301
<i>Team Renata versus Team Madeline.</i>

46:42.593 --> 46:44.762
<i>BERNARD". The battle lines
were drawn right there.</i>

46:45.596 --> 46:49.100
<i>So we're like
seriously using the word "murder"?</i>

48:10.473 --> 48:12.475
(MUSIC PLAYING)
